                    <span>If you are a professor wishing to find a book to use in class, look elsewhere.<p>If you are a student at NDSU wishing to take this class, find a different teacher than Dr. Martin.<p>The book, and teacher, poorly communicates the subjects at hand. The writing style is among the worst I've seen. <p>Go with 'Introduction to the Theory of Computation' by Michael Sipser.<p>Nuff said</span>
                  
              
